Officers set up roadblocks across the province on Friday night, checking for roadworthiness, documentation and driver sobriety. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape traffic authorities have arrested more than a dozen motorists since the start of the weekend. Officers set up roadblocks across the province on Friday night, checking for roadworthiness, documentation and driver sobriety. Ten drivers were taken into custody for being under the influence of alcohol. Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa says officers also nabbed two people for speeding. We also arrested one person for fraud and a drunk pedestrian in Vredenburg. Another driver was also arrested in Worcester for being in possession of false documentation. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)